	<text xstart="15" ystart="56" xend="320" yend="508" layer="3" starttime="0" font="Calibri" fontcolour="#000000" fontsize="16"><textbody italic="true" bold="false" underlined="false"><textstring>- Combat is handled as an Opposed Test.\n- Attacker rolls attack skill +/- modifiers.\n- Melee: Defender rolls Fray or melee skill +/- modifiers.\n- Ranged: Defender rolls (Fray ÷ 2, round down) +/- modifiers.\n- If attacker succeeds and rolls higher than the defender, the attack hits.\n- Critical hits are armour-defeating (armour does not apply).\n- Armour is reduced by the attack’s Armour Penetration value (AP).\n-The weapon’s damage is reduced by the targets modified Armour rating (unless the attack is armour-defeating).\n-If the damage exceeds the target’s Wound Threshold, a wound is also scored. (If the damage exceeds the Wound Threshold by multiple factors, multiple wounds are inflicted).</textstring>
	</textbody>
	</text>
